Date:  4/6/1983
Source:  Listener (New Zealand Listener)
Author:
Vol / Page:  55
Edition:
Quote:  Among the authentic local baking-terms the one I find most evocative is the Tararua biscuit. It comes in high-fibre, high-calorie slabs generally baked by young males in secret when Mum is watching TV. Two generations of trampers swear by its life-sustaining qualities and two generations of Wellington dentists must have made a tidy income from its inroads.
